  {
    "hotel_id": "1179332",
    "hotel_url": "https://www.agoda.com/1969-blue-sky-hotel_3/hotel/taichung-tw.html",
    "name": "BlueSky Hotel",
    "detail": "The interior design is modern and stunning. It is referred to as “elegant industrial.” I have stayed at some hotels designed as “industrial” with exposed pipes and other hardware and they felt cold and uninviting. This hotel is different. It retains a warm inviting feeling but encompasses many unique industrial design features. You will realize this is a modern hotel when you see the Nespresso coffee maker. I believe it is the first one I have seen in Taiwan. This as a boutique type hotel so you won’t have a doorman opening the door for you, but that door! An amazing piece of engineering. You will still have great service you expect from a Taiwan hotel. My stay included the buffet breakfast. It may have been lacking in quantity of items, but what I sampled was very good. Some items even showed a creative talent. I which there were more bakery items like croissants or western style cereal. They advertise a “lounge” on the second floor. It is not a lounge that serves drinks. It is only a sitting room with a jukebox that plays CDs. Overall, an amazing hotel that is a 10 minute walk from Taichung train station. At less than 100US for a Luxury room, this represented an excellent value or in the local culture, a great CP value. ",
